## Overview

This document defines the QA standards for **{{PROJECT_NAME}}**. All automated testing, manual test plans, and the QA agent behavior must comply with the rules below.

**Primary test framework:** `{{QA_TEST_FRAMEWORK}}`
**Coverage threshold:** `{{QA_COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}`
**QA scope:** `{{QA_SCOPE}}`

---

## Test Strategy

### Scope

The QA scope (`{{QA_SCOPE}}`) determines which test layers are active:

| Scope value | Layers covered |
|-------------|---------------|
| `all`       | Unit + Integration + E2E |
| `backend`   | Unit + Integration (backend only) |
| `frontend`  | Unit + Component + E2E (frontend only) |
| `e2e`       | End-to-end tests only |
| `unit`      | Unit tests only |

Focus areas for this project: `{{QA_FOCUS_AREAS}}`

### Test Types

#### Unit Tests
- Test a single function, class, or component in isolation
- Mock all external dependencies (databases, APIs, external services)
- Fast to run — no I/O or network calls
- Located alongside the source file (e.g., `user.service.test.ts` next to `user.service.ts`)

#### Integration Tests
- Test multiple units together (e.g., service + repository)
- May hit a real database (test database or in-memory)
- Verify contracts between layers
- Located in a dedicated `tests/integration/` folder

#### End-to-End (E2E) Tests
- Test full user flows through the running application
- Use `{{QA_TEST_FRAMEWORK}}` to drive the browser or API
- Cover the critical paths first (happy path + key error cases)
- Located in `tests/e2e/` or `e2e/`

### Coverage Requirements

- **Minimum threshold:** `{{QA_COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}`
- Coverage is measured on: statements, branches, functions, lines
- Coverage reports are generated on every CI run
- PRs that drop coverage below the threshold are **blocked** (see [Quality Gates](#quality-gates))
- Exclude from coverage: generated files, migrations, seed scripts, type-only files

